# Warp Terminal Configuration

This directory contains shared [Warp](https://warp.dev) terminal configuration for
the **{{ project_name }}** development team.

## Contents

| Path | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `settings.toml` | Recommended team terminal settings (agent profiles, appearance) |
| `themes/{{ project_slug }}.yaml` | Custom project color theme |
| `workflows/*.yaml` | Parameterized command workflows accessible from Warp |
| `notebooks/onboarding.md` | Interactive onboarding notebook |
| `AGENTS.md` | Warp Agent Mode project rules |

## Setup

Settings and themes are deployed automatically by `scripts/install/install-warp.zsh`.

To deploy manually:

```bash
# macOS
cp settings.toml ~/.warp/settings.toml
cp themes/*.yaml ~/.warp/themes/

# Linux
cp settings.toml ~/.config/warp-terminal/settings.toml
cp themes/*.yaml ~/.local/share/warp-terminal/themes/

# Windows
copy settings.toml %LOCALAPPDATA%\warp\Warp\config\settings.toml
copy themes\*.yaml %APPDATA%\warp\Warp\data\themes\
```

## Workflows

Warp workflows are parameterized commands shared across the team. They appear in
Warp's command palette and support tab-completion for arguments.

Available workflows:

- **Start Development** — `task dev`
- **Bootstrap Project** — Full environment setup
- **Docker Compose** — Container lifecycle management
- **Run All Tests** — Full test suite
- **Backend Tests** — By type (unit/integration/property)
- **Type Check** — Backend + frontend type checking
- **Lint & Format** — Code quality enforcement
- **Security Audit** — Vulnerability scanning
- **Database Migration** — Schema management
- **Deploy** — Environment-specific deployment
- **Profile** — CPU/memory profiling
- **Registry** — Naming registry operations
- **Frontend Build** — Mode-specific builds
- **Health Check** — Service health verification
- **Git Workflow** — Common git operations
{% if use_ai %}- **AI Ops** — AI infrastructure management
